# ============================================================

# SMART INFRASTRUCTURE WEBSITE — AI CODING RULES

# Apply EVERY rule below on ALL tasks, ALL responses.

# These rules are non-negotiable and override any defaults.

# ============================================================

# ── TECH STACK ───────────────────────────────────────────────

- React 19 + JSX only. All component files use `.jsx` extension. NEVER `.tsx`.
- Tailwind CSS for all styling. No per-component CSS files.
- React Router v6 for all navigation.
- Plain JavaScript only. No TypeScript — no `interface`, no `type`, no generics.

# ── DESIGN TOKENS — NEVER HARDCODE COLORS ───────────────────

- Navy : bg-navy / text-navy (NOT #001439)
- Blue : bg-primary-blue / text-primary-blue (NOT #2A8CD5)
- Sky : bg-sky-accent / text-sky-accent (NOT #9FCCFF)
- Heading font : Segoe UI
- Body font : Inter

# ── FOLDER PLACEMENT DECISION TREE ──────────────────────────

Before placing ANY file, run this tree:

Used on 2+ UNRELATED pages?
YES → src/components/ui/
NO →
Layout shell (Navbar, Footer, TopBar)?
YES → src/components/common/[Name]/
NO →
Shared across 2+ pages in the SAME section?
YES → src/pages/[SectionGroup]/components/
NO → src/pages/[PageName]/components/

# ── CANONICAL FOLDER MAP ─────────────────────────────────────

src/
├── components/
│ ├── common/ # Navbar, Footer, TopBar, Button
│ └── ui/ # Reusable across 2+ unrelated pages
├── pages/ # One folder per page
│ └── [PageName]/
│ ├── [PageName].jsx
│ ├── index.js
│ └── components/
├── layouts/ # MainLayout.jsx, AdminLayout.jsx
├── data/ # ALL static data arrays — never in components
├── hooks/ # useXxx.js
├── config/ # routes.js, siteConfig.js
├── services/ # api.js, contactService.js
├── utils/ # formatDate.js, validators.js
└── styles/ # index.css (Tailwind directives)

# ── NAMING CONVENTIONS ───────────────────────────────────────

- Component files → PascalCase.jsx (e.g. SectionHeader.jsx)
- Data files → camelCase.js (use .jsx ONLY if file contains JSX/SVG)
- Hook files → camelCase.js, prefixed with `use` (e.g. useScrollPosition.js)
- Utility files → camelCase.js (e.g. formatDate.js)
- Every page folder → MUST have index.js re-exporting the page default

# ── COMPONENT EXPORT RULES ───────────────────────────────────

- Shared / UI components → named export: `export function SectionHeader() {}`
- Page components → default export: `export default function HomePage() {}`
- NEVER mix these up.

# ── IMPORT RULES ─────────────────────────────────────────────

- ALWAYS use `@/` alias for any cross-folder import.
- NEVER use deep relative paths like `../../../components/`.

  ✅ import SectionHeader from '@/components/ui/SectionHeader';
  ✅ import { products } from '@/data/products/products';
  ✅ import { ROUTES } from '@/config/routes';

  ❌ import SectionHeader from '../../../components/ui/SectionHeader';

# ── STANDARD FILE IMPORT ORDER ───────────────────────────────

1. React imports
2. Third-party library imports
3. Internal component imports (use @/ alias)
4. Data imports

# ── PAGE COMPONENT TEMPLATE ──────────────────────────────────

Every page must follow this shell exactly:

import MainLayout from '@/layouts/MainLayout';
import GetInTouchForm from '@/components/ui/GetInTouchForm';
// ... other shared + page-specific imports

export default function PageName() {
return (
<MainLayout>
<HeroSection />
<ContentSection />
<GetInTouchForm />
</MainLayout>
);
}

- ALWAYS wrap page in <MainLayout>. NEVER add <Navbar> or <Footer> inside a page.
- ALWAYS create index.js: `export { default } from './PageName';`

# ── ANTI-DUPLICATION — CHECK REGISTRY BEFORE WRITING ANY JSX ─

Before writing ANY new component or JSX block, ask:

1. Section with label + heading + subtitle? → USE SectionHeader
2. Contact form? → USE GetInTouchForm
3. Expandable FAQ list? → USE FAQAccordion
4. Product card with image? → USE ProductCard
5. Card with icon + title + description? → USE ServiceCard
6. Detail/sub-page back link? → USE BackButton
7. Row of stats/numbers? → USE StatsBar

If the answer is YES to any — import the component, NEVER recreate it.

## Shared Components Registry

| Component      | Path                           | Props                                         |
| -------------- | ------------------------------ | --------------------------------------------- |
| SectionHeader  | @/components/ui/SectionHeader  | label, title, subtitle?, align? (def: center) |
| GetInTouchForm | @/components/ui/GetInTouchForm | (none)                                        |
| FAQAccordion   | @/components/ui/FAQAccordion   | items: { question, answer }[]                 |
| ProductCard    | @/components/ui/ProductCard    | id, image, name, category, to                 |
| ServiceCard    | @/components/ui/ServiceCard    | icon, title, description, href?               |
| BackButton     | @/components/ui/BackButton     | (none)                                        |
| StatsBar       | @/components/ui/StatsBar       | stats: { value, label }[]                     |

# ── ROUTING RULES ────────────────────────────────────────────

- ALL route path strings live in `src/config/routes.js` as named ROUTES constants.
- NEVER hardcode a URL string in <Link to=""> or navigate().
- ALL pages must be lazy-loaded in src/router.jsx.

  ✅ <Link to={ROUTES.PRODUCTS}>View All</Link>
  ✅ <Link to={ROUTES.PRODUCT_DETAIL.replace(':id', product.id)}>View</Link>
  ❌ <Link to="/products">View All</Link>

Adding a new page — always do ALL 3 steps:
A. Add constant to src/config/routes.js
B. Add lazy import + <Route> to src/router.jsx
C. Create page folder with PageName.jsx + index.js + components/

# ── DATA LAYER RULES ─────────────────────────────────────────

- NO data arrays or objects inside component files.
- If you write `const items = [...]` inside a .jsx file → STOP and move it to src/data/.
- ALL static data belongs in src/data/ files.
- Product IDs must be NUMBERS, not strings. e.g. `id: 1` NOT `id: 'smart-energy-meter'`

Data files registry:
src/data/products/products.js → id: number, name, category, image, description, specs
src/data/ourProducts/...js → Product categories
src/data/featuredProducts/featuredProducts.js
src/data/heroSlides/heroSlides.js
src/data/industries/industries.js
src/data/projects/projects.js
src/data/partners/partners.js
src/data/navigation/navigation.js
src/data/services.jsx → .jsx because entries contain inline SVG icons
src/data/languages/languages.jsx → .jsx because entries contain inline SVG flags
src/data/notFound/notFound.js

## Site Constants — NEVER Hardcode

Company name, phone, email, address, social links → import from `src/config/siteConfig.js`

✅ import { siteConfig } from '@/config/siteConfig';
<a href={`tel:${siteConfig.phone}`}>{siteConfig.phone}</a>

❌ <a href="tel:+18555XXXXXXX">+(855) XXX XXX XXX</a>

# ── TAILWIND CSS RULES ───────────────────────────────────────

- Use Tailwind utility classes exclusively.
- NO inline style={{}} — except for truly dynamic values Tailwind cannot express.
- Use responsive prefixes: sm: md: lg: xl:
- Use `text-md` or larger for all text. Do not use any text size below `text-md`.
- Use design token classes from tailwind.config.js (e.g. text-navy, bg-primary-blue).
- NEVER use arbitrary pixel values like w-[347px] for layout — use spacing scale.
- Arbitrary values are acceptable only for specific image dimensions.

# ── PROPS RULES ──────────────────────────────────────────────

- Destructure at the function signature: `function Card({ title, image, href })`
- Provide defaults for optional props: `function Card({ align = 'center' })`
- NEVER hardcode content strings — they must come from props or src/data/.

# ── HARD RULES TABLE — NEVER BREAK ──────────────────────────

| Rule                    | Wrong                        | Correct                          |
| ----------------------- | ---------------------------- | -------------------------------- |
| HTML class attribute    | class="..."                  | className="..."                  |
| TypeScript syntax       | interface Props, : string    | Plain JS only                    |
| Per-component CSS       | import './Card.css'          | Tailwind classes only            |
| React function type     | React.FC                     | Plain function                   |
| Shared component export | export default SectionHeader | export function SectionHeader    |
| Page component export   | export function HomePage     | export default function HomePage |
| Navbar/Footer in pages  | <Navbar /> inside page       | Injected by MainLayout only      |
| Hardcoded route strings | <Link to="/products">        | <Link to={ROUTES.PRODUCTS}>      |
| Data in component files | const items = [...] in .jsx  | Import from src/data/            |
| Hardcoded colors        | #001439 or #2A8CD5           | text-navy, bg-primary-blue       |
| Hardcoded contact info  | "+1 855 XXX XXXX"            | siteConfig.phone                 |
| Product ID as string    | id: 'smart-energy-meter'     | id: 1                            |

# ── NEW PAGE CHECKLIST ───────────────────────────────────────

When creating any new page, follow in order:

[ ] Step 1 — Identify shared components to import (run anti-duplication checks above)
[ ] Step 2 — Decide file placement using decision tree
[ ] Step 3 — Create folder: PageName.jsx + index.js + components/
[ ] Step 4 — Write index.js first
[ ] Step 5 — Write page shell wrapped in <MainLayout>
[ ] Step 6 — Write page-specific section components (named exports, data from src/data/)
[ ] Step 7 — Register route in routes.js AND router.jsx
[ ] Step 8 — Final sanity check:
[ ] No <Navbar> or <Footer> inside the page
[ ] No contact form markup rebuilt from scratch
[ ] No section header rebuilt inline
[ ] No data arrays defined inside any .jsx file
[ ] All <Link> and navigate() calls use ROUTES constants
[ ] All cross-folder imports use @/ alias
[ ] Shared/UI components use named exports
[ ] Page default export wrapped in <MainLayout>
[ ] index.js exists in the page folder
[ ] Route registered in both routes.js and router.jsx

# Project Rules

- Generate code that is optimized for performance, safety, security, and SEO.
- Prefer simple, efficient implementations that avoid unnecessary re-renders, duplicate work, and wasted assets.
- Validate and sanitize all user-facing input, avoid unsafe patterns, and never hardcode secrets or sensitive data.
- Use semantic HTML, meaningful headings, descriptive alt text, accessible labels, and a crawlable page structure.
- Keep changes maintainable, lint-friendly, and consistent with the existing codebase conventions.
